## 4. RBAC & Security Access Scoping
Security is strictly applied. All database queries must be scoped to the user's explicit list of authorized locations. If not resolved, a deny-all response ensures no accidental data exposure.

```mermaid
flowchart TD
    %% Styling
    classDef security fill:#ffebee,stroke:#c62828,stroke-width:2px;
    classDef database fill:#e8f5e9,stroke:#2e7d32,stroke-width:2px;

    User[Authenticated User Session]:::security
    Auth[Load allowedLocations from user profile]:::security
    Check{allowedLocations Empty?}:::security
    
    Check -->|Yes| Deny[Deny-All: Empty Result Set]:::security
    Check -->|No| BuildQuery[Inject location_id filter into query]:::security
    
    BuildQuery -->|WHERE location_id IN ...| RunQuery[Execute SQL Database Query]:::database
    RunQuery --> FilterPII[Strip Customer PII: Emails, Phone numbers]:::security
    FilterPII --> ReturnData[Send Secure Response]:::security
```
